Table of Our Personal Data Collection and Use Practices
1. Territorial Restrictions
The Services are controlled and operated from the United States. The Services audio and subscription services under this Policy are intended for use only by residents of the United States, except for (i) certain podcast-only subscriptions and content described below or (ii) any online merchandise store operated by Sirius XM. Please see the terms of service set forth respectively in the Sirius XM Customer Agreement at siriusxm.com and the Pandora Services Terms of Use at pandora.com. NOTE: If you are a resident of Canada, your Sirius XM service is governed by your Customer Agreement with Sirius XM Canada Inc., and your use of the services offered through Sirius XM Canada is governed by the Sirius XM Canada Privacy Policy.
If you are not a resident of the United States, please do not interact with the Services. To enforce our territorial limits, we may collect data associated with a device to determine the country from which the device is accessing the Services. If we receive data from your device’s location indicating that you are outside the United States, we may block your access to the Services from that particular device. If you attempt to access the Services when you are outside the United States, we will use your IP address to determine the territory of access in order to enforce our agreements and terms of use and may deny access to content or other Services.
International Transfer of Personal Data:
Sirius XM Podcast Content may be accessible to you through a Third Party Service in any territory that the Third Party Service operates within, including the Sirius XM Podcast + subscription offered through Apple. When you access the Sirius XM Podcast + Subscription on Apple or Sirius XM Podcast Content on another Third Party Service, including from outside of the United States, Sirius XM may collect and use some personal data about the delivery of the podcast as set forth in this Policy, including but not limited to the IP address and device requesting the podcast and how long it was listened to, as described below in Section 10 “Supplemental Information for Listeners of Sirius XM Podcast Content”. If you choose to access the Sirius XM Podcast Content from outside of the United States, or if you provide any personal data directly to us through the Team Coco, 99% Invisible or any other Sirius XM consumer website such as the Sirius XM merchandise store, or any interaction with Team Coco or 99% Invisible directly, you understand that your data will be transferred to and processed in the United States, where data protection and privacy regulations may not offer the same level of protection as in other parts of the world such as the European Union.
In addition, Sirius XM owns and operates online stores for retail purchase of merchandise licensed by Sirius XM (the “Sirius XM Stores”). Access to and use of the Sirius XM Stores is permitted from outside the United States. Sirius XM operates the Sirius XM Stores from the United States and uses service providers in the United States, Canada and the European Union. If you choose to view products and/or purchase merchandise from any Sirius XM Store, you consent to have your personal data transferred to and processed by Sirius XM and its Store service providers in any of these locations.
By using any of the above listed Services in this section, you consent to the transfer to and processing of your personal data in the United States. Data collected or used by a Third Party Service is governed by the privacy policy of the Third Party Service.
2. Personal Data We Collect
We collect data that is linked to or can be linked to a specific individual for the purposes described in this Policy. This data, called “personal data” (sometimes also referred to as “personal information”), may be provided directly by you to us, provided to us by third parties, such as automotive manufacturers or dealers, providers of automotive services, retailers, data providers, advertisers or promotional partners, or other advertising entities, or collected from you automatically through your service usage, cookies, and other technologies. We may combine personal data we collect from these sources or through our various Services.
De-identified Data
. We may de-identify your personal data using any of a variety of means, such as by removing identifying characteristics and/or blending your data with data about other individuals. Such de-identified data can no longer be associated to you and is considered non-personal to the full extent allowed by applicable law. We utilize technical and operational processes to maintain and use de-identified data and do not make attempts to re-identify it. We may use and share any non-personal information with third parties for any purpose in our discretion and as permitted by law, including for advertising, research and marketing purposes, but we require any third party receiving de-identified information from us to maintain the information as de-identified and not reassociate it to any individual. If we combine non-personal data with personal data, we treat the combined information as personal data and subject to this Policy.
3. Summary of Sirius XM Key Personal Data Practices
This section and the next present a summary of our key personal data practices. For more detail, please see the Sirius XM Data Collection and Use Table at the end of this Policy for the
(1) categories of personal data we collect, (2) purposes for which we collect that information, (3) categories of third parties to whom that information may be disclosed for a business purpose and (4) categories of third parties to whom the information may be sold for monetary value or other valuable consideration or shared for cross contextual behavioral advertising/targeted advertising.
We encourage you to read the Table carefully. Please also
review Section 4
“More About our Data Practices”
for certain specific types of data collection and use.
We collect personal data about you from you directly, automatically through your use of the Services, and from third parties
. The categories of personal data we collect include: 1. Registration Data, 2. Vehicle Data, 3. Payment Data, 4. Sensitive Personal Data, 5. Other Demographic Data, 6. Transaction Information, 7. Listening Preferences, 8. Account Information and Settings, 9. Device Data, 10. Audio and Visual Data, and 11. Geolocation Data (which may include precise geolocation only with your consent).
We use personal data
to deliver products and Services and facilitate your access to the Services, to manage your account and subscriptions, to personalize your listening, marketing and advertising experiences, and to send you information from us or on behalf of certain third parties. We also use personal data to troubleshoot and improve the Services, to perform market research and enhance our marketing effectiveness through modeling and optimization, to develop new products and services, and to maintain and protect our systems and your data. If you access the Services using an in-vehicle SiriusXM radio, please also
review Section 8 “Supplemental Information for Users of SiriusXM In-Vehicle Services”
for in-vehicle specific information. If you use the Pandora Services, please
review Section 9 “Supplemental Information for Users of Pandora Services”
.
If you access Sirius XM Podcast Content through a Sirius XM Podcast + standalone subscription or through a Third Party Service, please review Section 10 “Supplemental information for Listeners of Sirius XM Podcast Content.”
We share your personal data
for business purposes with our subsidiaries, third party service providers, vendors and licensors, other Sirius XM users when you provide access to your subscription, and unaffiliated third-party businesses with whom we have relationships for business and advertising purposes. Sirius XM does not sell your personal data
for monetary compensation. For more details, please
review Section 4 “Disclosures to Third Parties”
.
Please note, if you choose to participate in community forums and similar features on the Services or make requests to on-air hosts, the information you share will become public and outside the scope of this Policy.
Sirius XM engages third party businesses for a variety of business and commercial purposes,
including service providers of technology, customer care support, marketing, shopping and shipping (such as Shopify) and payment processing (such as but not limited to Apple, Google, and Stripe Inc.). Please note that collection and use of payment information by third party merchants and payment processors is subject to the privacy policy and terms of the respective third party. For example, Stripe Inc.’s collection and processing of payment information is governed by the Stripe Privacy Policy located at https://stripe.com/privacy.
Sirius XM works with advertisers, advertising agencies, and providers of ad-related services
for targeted advertising. Providers of ad-related services such as attribution, measurement, and analytics, may set and access their own tracking technologies (like cookies tags or pixels) on your device. They may use this information to serve and measure performance of ads for the Services placed by us on third party publishers and channels, to serve and measure performance of third party advertisers’ ads on the Services, and to provide us with information regarding the use of the Services and the effectiveness of ads. For more information, including your opt-out choices, please
review Section 5 “Third Party Advertising and Analytics/Privacy Controls”
and the information set forth in the Table at the end of this Privacy Policy. This practice may be considered sale or regulated sharing under certain US state laws and residents of those states may have additional rights. For more information, please
review Section 14 “State Specific Rights”.
4. More About our Data Practices
Here is additional detail about some specific data practices listed in the Table in Section 15.
Personal Data We Collect Directly From or About You.
You may provide us with the information described in the Table in Section 15 directly when you engage with the Services, such as signing up for an account online, through an application, or interact with a Listener Care agent. We also may collect personal data directly from you when you choose to provide to it, such as when you respond to a survey or when you conduct a transaction, such as purchasing merchandise from a Sirius XM store.
Inferences.
We use proprietary and licensed modeling tools and algorithms to infer additional information about you from your listening history, demographic data or other data that we collect directly from or indirectly about you to personalize your service, marketing and advertising. We do not use inferences to make determinations that would have a legally significant impact on you.
Profiles.
SiriusXM-brand subscriptions may allow the creation of in-vehicle profiles for individual listeners. If you are the primary account holder of a SiriusXM-brand subscription, you are responsible for access by anyone whose profile you allow to connect to your Sirius XM Service, and the terms of your subscription plan, the Sirius XM Customer Agreement and this Policy will apply to their use of your subscription. If you set up a profile for listening use on a Sirius XM-brand Service, you provide us with personal data and agree that such personal data and any listening and service usage information associated to your profile may be collected and processed to support the profile features. We do not use profile personal data for advertising or share profile personal data with third parties other than service providers. If it is technically possible and with your express consent, we may add your profile data to an account created explicitly for you when you subscribe to a SiriusXM-brand Service. The data on your subscription account will become subject to the full range of terms of this Policy.
Live Real Time Chat.
The Services may offer you a Customer Support Chat, which will record, use, and retain your information provided, as well as the communications within the chat, for purposes of assisting you during the conversation, provide related support for your account, subscription, or services, to improve our products and services, and for marketing purposes. During a Customer Support Chat, you may interact with a generative artificial intelligence. The chat session, including any information contained within it, may be retained and used by the generative AI application to learn and improve its ability to provide support to customers of the Services. If you do not consent to such recording, use and retention, please do not use the chat assistance feature.
Photos and Audio.
We may allow you to post photos or audio files to the Services or we may collect photos or audio from another interaction you have with us, such as your call interaction with a Listener Care agent, your call-in to a show or host, or your participation at a Sirius XM or Pandora live event. We do not process your photos or audio to create a record of facial geometry or use as them as a means for facial or voice recognition, facial surveillance, or in any other way as a biometric identifier. We collect your voice command when you make a verbal request to the Services; we process your voice in order to execute your request and for analysis of the success rate of the request for product improvement. Your voice command is not used to identify you individually and is not retained in association with you or your subscription. Audio that we collect from you may be shared with a third-party service provider for transcription.
Please note that to the extent that you post your photos or audio publicly onto community spaces on the Services, they will be public. In addition, when you post or share photos, videos or audio on social media or other third-party platforms, we do not control the actions of those third parties, and their use of such media will be governed by their own privacy policies.
Personal Data We Receive or Collect from Third Parties.
We may receive information about you from service providers, third parties with whom we have a business relationship (such as vehicle manufacturers, dealers, vehicle repair companies, sponsors, or licensors), retailers, content distribution platforms, advertising networks and agencies, advertising technology companies, marketing companies, data providers, sources of publicly available information, governmental or quasi-governmental agencies or organizations, and other users of the Services (such as community users, when users provide your information to gift you one of our products, share content with you, “refer a friend” or similar programs that we may offer). We may combine and store the supplemental information with other information we may have already received or collected from you, for use as set forth in this Policy.
Data We Collect Automatically: Device Data.
We, our service providers, or third parties with whom we have a business relationship may automatically collect and/or store certain data about your device when you visit or interact with the Services (“Device Data”). This Device Data may be stored and/or accessed from your computer, tablet, mobile device, or other device
(including streaming media players, gaming consoles, home audio systems, connected speakers or other smart devices, and wearable devices) whenever you visit or interact with the Services. Device Data may include, but is not limited to:
Your IP address, mobile or connected device identifier when made available by the device manufacturer
Information about the device such as model, operating system version, date/time of access, mobile network information
Approximate location of your device using location inferred from IP address or if you choose to provide it (such as country, city, state or zip code)
Precise Geolocation (e.g., longitude/latitude, or proximity to beacon) only when you grant permission through your device settings.
How you use and interact with the Services. This information will depend on the format and subscription through which you access the Services and may include the webpage, link or advertisement that referred you to the Service you are visiting, areas of the Services that you visit or use, access times and time zone, listening behavior (channel preferences, stations and playlists you create or listen to), search terms, downloads, content you listen to or view and duration of viewing, marine or aviation data, driving patterns and condition.
Device Data may be collected through the following technologies:
Cookies and Local Storage
.
Cookies and local storage are text files placed within a web browser or application on a device when it is used to visit the Services. Certain web browsers and browser add-ons may provide additional local data storage mechanisms.
We may use cookies and similar technologies to help keep your use of the Services more secure, to study usage patterns on the Services, to study the effectiveness of our customer communications, to maintain the integrity of the Services, to measure crash analytics and other maintenance related information, to manage and measure the performance of advertisements displayed on or delivered by or through the Services or by Sirius XM on other sites, and to personalize your experience through the Services, such as to recognize you when you return to the Services. Most browsers provide you with the ability to disable, decline, or clear cookies and local storage; please check your browser’s settings for further information. Some cookies are necessary for the functionality of the website (“Essential Cookies”). These cookies may not be disabled.
In addition, third parties may place cookies on our websites to improve and optimize our advertising campaigns or those of third party advertisers. Some third party advertisers may embed cookies or tags within the advertising creative that is served through the Services. These cookies or tags send information to the advertiser or its services providers to manage and measure the performance of their campaigns.
You may manage whether or not to accept cookies (other than Essential Cookies) on websites operated by Sirius XM through the Manage Cookies link on each respective website. Note that such cookie preferences do not transfer between browsers and must be reset for each browser or device that you use to access a site. For more information about cookies, please visit
https://www.aboutcookies.org
.
Pixel Tags.
Small graphic images or other web programming code (also known as web beacons or pixel tags or 1x1 GIFs or clear GIFs) may be included in our web pages and email messages. These technologies are used to understand how end users interact with the Services, including to count visitors to the Services, to review the effectiveness of our offers and ad campaigns, to count how many of our email messages were opened, or to count how many particular products were viewed. The information we collect through this technology may include the first date and time you open our email, and whether you click any links included in our email.
Embedded Scripts.
Siriusxm.com may use an embedded script to collect information about your usage of the online Service, such as the links you click on or the time you spend on a part of the page.
Session Replay Technology.
Sirius XM may record through session replay technology details of your interactions with the Services such as what pages you visit on the website, how long you visit those pages, what sections of the page you spend the most time reviewing, and any links you click or information you provide. We use this information for our internal business purposes, such as for website analytics, to improve the Services and our products and services, and to address functionality issues.
Data Collected Through Mobile and Connected Devices:
Software Development Kits (“SDKs”).
We and certain third parties with whom we have a relationship to facilitate our Service and advertising operations collect data through the use of embedded scripts and tools provided in SDKs. These SDKs are included in the app itself and may collect information when you install the mobile app or access the Services through mobile devices. Such data may include hardware model, operating system and version, device ID, mobile network information, and application usage behavior. Some Device Data may be deemed personal data, to the extent that it remains associated with a device identifiable to you in some way. When this is the case, we treat Device Data as personal data. Device Data is used for the business and commercial purposes disclosed in this Policy, such as to deliver and personalize the Services to you, to understand service usage and improve the Services, to debug, troubleshoot, prevent fraud and other security related purposes, to identify you across devices for service and advertising purposes, and to facilitate your request to log in to the Service through a third party or social media platform, conduct a transaction through a third party or share content with a friend or other third party account. Settings specific to your mobile or connected device manufacturer may allow you to change or block the transmission of your device ID and other Device Data. Please see the privacy policy of your device manufacturer for details. Sirius XM does not sell personal data collected through SDKs to third parties nor allow third parties to collect such information directly for monetary consideration.
Connected Devices.
The Services may also be accessed through third party devices such as connected set top boxes or media players, speakers or other smart devices, gaming consoles, or other similar devices. Sirius XM does not control these devices, your underlying subscription with that device, or their collection and use of your personal data, including in relationship to targeted advertising they may deliver through a connected device. Please contact the manufacturer of the connected device or purveyor of the connected services for information on their privacy practices and policies.
Sharing with Third Parties
We may share personal data we have collected about you in the circumstances described below or elsewhere in the Policy. Please note that we are not responsible for the privacy practices of any third party with whom you interact or who interacts with you directly. If you decide that you do not want to receive communications from a third party, or have questions about their privacy practices, you will need to contact the third party.
A.
Other SiriusXM Users
Personal data on your account or subscription may be accessible to others that you allow to interact with your account/subscription. It is solely your choice whether or not you allow other individuals to have access to your account or sign-in credentials. This includes individuals whom you allow to use or access any streaming account associated with your SiriusXM brand audio subscription. Please note that if you leave your profile open on an active SiriusXM in-vehicle account, other drivers of the vehicle may be able to view certain profile information. You are responsible for managing your profile, including removing it from a vehicle. You may do so through your
Profile Management Portal
.
Visit
https://www.siriusxm.com/help/profiles
-
2
for more information.
B.
Subsidiaries
Sirius XM may share personal data collected in conjunction with the Services with our subsidiaries for business, analytical, marketing, operational and advertising purposes and to offer, provide, and improve services and products offered both individually and jointly.
C.
Unaffiliated Third-Party Business Relationships
We may share your email address with unaffiliated third parties with whom we have a business relationship for ours or for their own business and advertising purposes. These third parties may include companies with whom we have marketing, licensing, sponsorship, product or service distribution, advertising or similar agreements. Such third party’s use of the personal data is subject to their privacy policy and data practices. You may opt-out of our sharing of your email address for third-party marketing through your Sirius XM Online Account
Center (for former or current SiriusXM audio subscribers) or by sending an email request to opt-out of sharing for third-party marketing to
privacy @siriusxm.com
or
privacy @pandora.com
, depending upon your subscription service. Opt-out requests received via these channels may take up to 15 business days to process. We may also share your personal data with unaffiliated third parties who provide services to help us find new audiences that will be most responsive to our services and communications and to help us optimize our marketing and advertising campaigns. We may use personal data, such as your email address, to create an identifier that is less identifiable to you directly (a pseudonym), that would be used to deliver you relevant or personalized advertising across unaffiliated websites, applications or devices without sharing your directly identifying information. Some states give their residents the right to opt-out of the sharing of personal data for use in targeted or behavioral advertising or in certain other contexts. Please see Section 14 “State-Specific Rights” for additional information.
Note that when you elect to accept a promotional offer for a service offered by a third party as part of a SiriusXM premium or other subscription service, we will only share information with that third party in order to confirm your eligibility for the associated service or as needed to maintain your access to the promotion, unless you consent to additional sharing or uses by the third party.
D.
Third Parties to Whom you Agree or Direct Us to Share Your Personal Data
We may share your personal data when you expressly consent or otherwise direct us to do so. For example, you may direct us to share your information with a Third Party Service in order to have access to Sirius XM Podcast + subscription content using the third party’s platform.
E.
Social Media and Other Third Party Platforms
We may facilitate interactions with social media or other third party platforms which may include the ability to “like” or “share” content. You may also have the opportunity to log in through or otherwise connect your third party platform account to your subscription Service. When you interact with these third party platforms through the Services, we will receive your personal data from the third party platform service and you agree to share data, which may be personal, about your interactions with the Service with that social media service. We may also receive personal data identifying you if other users of social media give us access to their profiles and you are one of their connections or “friends.”
Personal data collected and stored by the third party is subject to that third party’s privacy practices, including, without limitation, whether the third party continues to share data with us, the types of data shared, and your choices with regard to what is visible to others on that third-party website or service. The third party may allow you to remove the application or feature; however we may retain data previously collected.
A third party platform or service, such as Facebook/Meta or TikTok, may place cookies on your device or and/or on the Services that collect information about your use of the Services, including your IP address or other device identifiers, and which pages you visit on the Services. The third party platform may be able to collect personal data about you on your visits to the Services regardless of whether or not you affirmatively interact with the feature and whether or not you are logged into (or have) an account with the third party platform. If you are logged out or do not have an account and visit a page with a social plug-in, your browser sends a more limited set of data, such as the webpage you are visiting, the date and time of your visit, and other browser-related information. Please
see Section 5
about how to manage cookies and tags online.
F.
Information You Disclose Publicly.
Services may offer message boards, chats, forums, and other public areas (“
Community Forums
”) where you can choose to interact with others and/or to post or submit comments, images, and content. Note that anything you choose to disclose in such a Community Forum is public. Similarly, any information you choose to post to a social media or third-party platform will be publicly available. This Policy does not apply to collection and use of such public information. Think carefully before you post and use caution before disclosing any personal data.
G.
Public Broadcasting/On Air.
If you provide us with personal data when making a request such as a birthday announcement, comments or suggestions, or content requests, we may use the personal data you provide in accordance with this Policy, including to announce your name and request on the air where relevant.
H.
Sweepstakes, Promotions, and Surveys
.
We may offer sweepstakes, contests, in-studio events, giveaways, research surveys and other promotions (any of which, a “Promotion”) that require registration or request additional information. By participating in a Promotion, you are agreeing to the provisions, conditions, or official rules that govern the Promotion, which may contain specific requirements (including, allowing the sponsor(s) of the Promotion to use your name, voice, likeness, or other indicia of persona in advertising or marketing materials where allowed by law). If you choose to enter a Promotion, personal data may be disclosed to third parties, to vendors facilitating the implementation of the Promotion, or to the public in connection with the administration of such Promotion, including in connection with winner selection, prize fulfillment, as required by law, or as permitted by the Promotion’s terms or official rules. I.
Third Parties in the Course of a Business Transition.
In the event one or more entities of Sirius XM goes through a business transition, Sirius XM reserves the right to disclose and transfer all personal data related to the respective Services to the full extent allowed by law (including, without limitation, during the course of any due diligence process): (i) to a subsequent owner, co-owner or operator of the Services; or (ii) in connection with a corporate merger, consolidation, restructuring, bankruptcy, the sale of certain of Sirius XM’s ownership interests, assets, or both, or other company change. By providing your information, you understand and agree that we may transfer such information to the acquiring entity without your further consent, except where required by law.
5. Third Party Advertising and Analytics/Privacy Controls
Sirius XM engages in third party business relationships, including with advertising companies, ad agencies, ad tech providers, measurement and attribution vendors, and analytics providers to place and display Sirius XM ads, to deliver third party ads on the Services, and to provide us with information regarding the use of the Services and ad effectiveness. In addition, some advertisers, agencies and ad tech vendors may utilize their own tracking technologies embedded in their ads or on your device, and they may otherwise collect or have access to data about your device and other information about you, some of which may be personal data under certain state laws. Some of these parties may collect personal data over time when you visit the Services or other online websites and services. We may share data that has been aggregated, de-identified, or pseudonymized or Device Data and location information with advertising companies, analytics providers, and attribution and measurement vendors, including for the purpose of serving you more relevant ads on and off the Services.
There are a variety of means and tools that allow you to place some limits on the collection and use of your personal data for targeted and/or cross device behavioral advertising by third parties, or by Sirius XM on other sites and applications:
Cookie Opt-Out Tools
.To disable sharing through cookies set on our site by third parties for advertising and analytics purposes, please adjust your settings by clicking on either Cookie Settings or Manage Cookies from the footer of our webpages.
NAI/DAA Opt-Out
. Some advertising companies are members of the Network Advertising Initiative (“NAI”) or Digital Advertising Alliance (“DAA”). The NAI provides information regarding targeted advertising, the
opt
-
out procedures of NAI members
,
and a tool to opt out from participating NAI members using your hashed email address for interest-based advertising. You may also want to visit the
DAA’s website
for more about targeted advertising and an opt-out for DAA-participating companies.
Mobile Device/AppChoices
. Mobile devices contain settings that may allow you to disable tracking advertising or analytics. If you are using an iOS-based device and do not want to receive advertisements personalized to you or your individual interests, you may be able to limit these advertisements by enabling “Limit Ad Tracking” on your iOS Device following the
instructions provided by Apple
.
If you are using an Android-based device and do not wish to receive advertisements personalized to you, you can visit
Google’s Ads Settings
page
from a browser on your Android-based device and make your choices there. In addition, the digital advertising industry has provided the ability for mobile users to register at
AppChoices
for their intent not to receive targeted advertising.
Google Analytics/Adobe Analytics.
We utilize Google Analytics and Adobe Analytics, which use cookies and similar technologies, to collect and analyze information about the use of the Services and report on activities and trends. These services may also collect information about the use of other websites, apps, and online services. You can
learn about Google’s
practices
,
and opt out of them by downloading the
Google Analytics opt
-
out browser add
-
on.
Learn about Adobe’s practices here.
Note that cookie settings and other technological controls are specific to the browser or device on which such control is implemented. When cookies or other such tags are disabled, we are not able to recognize you when you use a different device to access the Services, and therefore cannot apply the settings from the initial device. You will need to manage your cookies and tag settings as well as any global privacy controls individually on each device with which you access the Services.
Please note, it is not possible to opt-out of all advertising on the Services. Advertising allows the Services to be delivered with limited ads at a generally lower subscription cost to you, or, with certain Services such as through the free ad-supported subscription tier of Pandora Services where available, at no additional subscription fee. Using any combination of the methods described here to opt-out of personalized or individually targeted advertising means only that you will not receive ads that are not tailored to you as a unique individual. By continuing to access the Services, you understand that even in light of your cookie settings and other opt-out choices, you will continue to receive ads, which may be delivered based on nonpersonalized information about the context or genre of the content to which you are listening, or the general demographic or behavioral interest profile of listeners of certain content, types of music, or titles or episodes of podcasts. You may also receive ads that are delivered generally to anyone in a certain geographical region or based on aggregated or non-personal data.
6. Your Choices and Opt Out Rights
A. Marketing Messages from Us.
You can manage how we use your personal data to contact you with regard to SiriusXM services by setting your contact preferences. Please visit
here
for additional information and instructions on how to do so. We may also provide you with options to manage how we communicate with you for marketing purposes for each of the Sirius XM Services through the contact or notification preferences under your account or profile settings online or in the respective app
.
Email.
You may unsubscribe from marketing emails and newsletters we send you through the opt-out link included in the footer of each such email. You may also opt-out of email marketing communications about SiriusXM satellite and streaming services using the SiriusXM Email Communications Preference Center at
https://pc2.mypreferences.com/SiriusXMV2/Customer/EmailRequest
.
Team Coco services users may opt out by sending an email to
legal@teamcoco.com
. 99% Invisible users may opt out through the opt-out link included in the footer of each e-mail or by contacting
contact@99pi.org
. We will continue to send you certain communications relating to your use of the Services, renewal notices, notices of changes to this Privacy Policy or other terms, or similar administrative and transactional messages.
Text Messages
. Sirius XM may use text messaging to send you offers, to facilitate account management or otherwise assist you in your access to the Services or your subscription. To the extent that you choose to stop receiving marketing texts, you may unsubscribe by replying “STOP” to the short code. Your consent to receive text messages will not be given to a third party for purposes related to other goods and services.
Push Notifications.
We may send promotional and non-promotional push notifications or alerts through the Services. You control whether you receive those messages in your device settings at any time.
B. Changing Your Information.
You are responsible for maintaining the accuracy of the information you submit to us, such as contact information you have provided for your account. You may be able make changes to your account information using the settings under your account.
SiriusXM.
Former or current subscribers to SiriusXM services may visit SiriusXM Listener Care online at http://www.siriusxm.com/contactus, or log into your Online Account Center to update your information. You may also call SiriusXM Listener Care at 1-855-539- 1-888-539-7474 and ask to update your information.
Pandora.
Pandora users may update their account information through their Settings page or contact the
User Support
team for assistance. You may find further instructions on how to modify your information by visiting help.pandora.com.
Team Coco.
If you joined the Team Coco mailing list or otherwise provided personal data to Team Coco that you would like to update, please contact
legal@teamcoco.com
.
99% Invisible.
If you subscribed to the 99% Invisible mailing list or otherwise interacted with 99% Invisible with personal data that you would like to update, please contact
contact@99pi.org
.
Note that when you edit your personal data or change your preferences, the previous information will be retained internally as part of the history of your account for analytical, administrative, legal and security purposes, or within backup media. If you have made any public postings on the Services including community forums or on social media platforms, those communications generally cannot be removed even if you cancel or deactivate your account.
C. For Users of SiriusXM Brand Audio Services
Telemarketing.
You may opt out of telemarketing sales calls by placing your phone number on our “Do Not Call” list using the instructions in our “Do Not Call” Policy available
here
and via the link from the footer of our home page on siriusxm.com. We may have more than one telephone number on record for you or your household members; you must specify all the phone numbers you are directing us to not call. Although your request will be processed immediately, it may take up to ten (10) days to remove your information from active telemarketing and solicitation lists that are in flight. Please note, even if you opt out of telemarketing sales calls, you may continue to receive calls for service and account-related matters.
Direct Mail.
If you prefer to not receive any marketing offers via direct mail, please visit the communications section in your account to indicate your preference. Please note such requests must be renewed every three (3) years. Please note, even if you tell us that you do not wish to receive Opting out of marketing direct mail from us, we will continue to send transactional communications relating to your subscription, account, or use of the Services, such as renewals, or administrative and services announcements, or communications that we have a legal obligation to send to you; we may continue to send such transactional communications by direct mail even if you opt-out of marketing mailings.
7. Security and Retention
Sirius XM takes commercially reasonable steps designed to secure your personal data; however no data transmission over the Internet, wireless transmission, or electronic storage of information can be guaranteed to be 100% secure. Sirius XM cannot ensure or warrant the security of any information we collect. You use the Services and provide us your information at your own risk.
We retain personal data for as long as it is necessary for the purposes set out in this Policy, including to provide the Services to you; to send you information related to Sirius XM, our products and services and your account; to conduct internal research, develop and improve new products and services; to exercise the choices and rights you have requested; to comply with our contractual obligations; to protect our legal rights and obligations, resolve disputes and enforce our Customer Agreement and Terms for Use or the terms for any other Service; and to comply with legal and regulatory requirements.
8. Supplemental Information for SiriusXM In-Vehicle Services Users
If you access the SiriusXM audio Services using in-vehicle hardware, please know that the following additional data collection and handling may apply:
Special Types of Data and Uses
SiriusXM audio Services may be delivered to your vehicle by satellite, through the wireless connection installed in your vehicle by your vehicle manufacturer, or a combination of these. Your make and model of vehicle determine what type of SiriusXM service delivery your vehicle is capable of. Please see your vehicle manufacturer or dealer for more information about the radio in your vehicle. We may collect information from the automotive manufacturer or from third parties about the vehicle and your ownership, such as your VIN, vehicle make, model, and year. We collect your license plate number only when you provide it to us directly as part of our authentication of you in association with your vehicle.
Satellite-Only Radios
. SiriusXM satellite-only radios can only receive data from the SiriusXM satellite network and cannot transmit service usage, location or other information from the radio or the vehicle.
A.
Information from the Vehicle
– We may collect information from the vehicle about the vehicle or your use of it, such as the VIN, vehicle make, model, and year, or vehicle usage metrics such as when the vehicle ignition starts or stops. We may also collect information about your use of the Services in the vehicle, such as which presets you use, how long you listen, when you navigate to the Service or away from it. For further information about our use of Vehicle Information, please see the
Table in Section 15 of this Policy
.
B.
Device Data from Enabled Radios
– Certain vehicles deploy technology that uses a combination of the SiriusXM satellite network and a wireless Internet connection by modem, or for certain electric vehicle manufacturers, employs a direct voice over IP wireless connection in the vehicle (each of these embedded systems, an “
Enabled Radio
”). When the modem in the vehicle is activated, an Enabled Radio may transmit Device Data and other service usage data such as your favorites and presets and data about your usage of the radio and our service, to Sirius XM, our service providers, and/or the automotive manufacturer. We use this information to maintain your settings, troubleshoot and improve service delivery and performance, personalize and facilitate the service we provide to you, offer you recommendations and other personalization options, tailor communications to your interests, personalize advertising delivered to you, and other purposes set forth in this Policy.
C.
Vehicle Location Data.
Sirius XM does not collect the precise geolocation of your vehicle and will not collect such information unless we expressly ask you and you provide your consent. You may have a setting in your vehicle to disable the capability of the vehicle to transmit geolocation. The effect of selecting this setting is determined by your vehicle manufacturer. Depending on the vehicle’s configuration, disabling the capability to transmit geolocation may also result in disabling the modem or other IP connectivity for Sirius XM or other features in your vehicle. With an active subscription, you may continue to receive Sirius XM satellite radio service without recommendations or other individual or personalized features. You will also lose access to profiles. You may also lose optimal functionality of Traffic, Travel Link and related infotainment services while driving. Please see your owner’s manual, or contact your vehicle manufacturer or dealer for more information.
Your Choices for Enabled Radios
– You may have privacy settings in your vehicle that can disable or limit the capability of the vehicle to transmit data from the modem in your vehicle including if applicable, geolocation. The effect of selecting this setting is determined by your vehicle manufacturer. Depending on the vehicle’s configuration, disabling the capability to transmit geolocation may also result in fully disabling the modem or other IP connectivity for Sirius XM or other features in your vehicle. Sirius XM does not collect the precise geolocation of your vehicle but does rely on other data transmitted to and from your vehicle to provide the full personalized experience of the Sirius XM audio service. If the modem is disabled and you maintain an active subscription, you may continue to receive Sirius XM satellite radio service without recommendations or other individual or personalized features. You will also lose access to profiles. You may also lose optimal functionality while driving of any Traffic Plans, TravelLink and related infotainment services to which you are subscribed. Please see your owner’s manual, or contact your vehicle manufacturer or dealer for more information.
9. Supplemental Information for Pandora Services Users
If you access and use the Pandora digital streaming audio service, please know that in addition to the collection, use, and sharing of personal data set forth in this Policy, the following apply:
A.
Your Choices Related to Your Pandora Profile
a.
Profile Visibility
- Your profile and listening activity are public. When the visibility of your profile is set to public, your listening activity is automatically published to your profile. For example, if you create a new station or thumb up a song, that activity will be posted in your profile and publicly visible. You may adjust your profile visibility settings by visiting help.pandora.com. Please note that changes to the visibility of your profile do not have any impact on the advertising you may see if you use the ad-supported version of the service.
b.
Cached Profiles on Search Engines
- Even upon deactivating your account or making your profile private, Internet search engines such as Google and Bing cache publicly available webpages for a period of time beyond our control and may make your deactivated or formerly public profile available to users of their services on their platforms until such time as they refresh their webpage cache. Please consult with the applicable search engine to determine how you may remove webpages from their webpage cache.
10. Supplemental Information for Listeners of Sirius XM Podcast Content
Sirius XM Podcast Content consists of podcasts created originally or licensed from other creators by Sirius XM. The Sirius XM Podcast Content may be available to you through the Services, or you may be able to access certain Sirius XM Podcast Content directly or through a Third Party Service that distributes podcast content to you through your account with that third party. You may also purchase a Sirius XM Podcast+ subscription from Sirius XM through a Third Party Service that works with the Podcast+ subscription. Through whichever distribution platform you access Sirius XM Podcast Content, Sirius XM may collect your IP address, coarse location such as country, state or city from which you are listening, information around the podcast usage (such as how long you listened) and certain Device Data, such as operating system and device type. In addition to uses set forth in this Policy for data collected by Sirius XM for the Services, collected information may be shared with creators, service providers, and advertising entities including technology companies, advertisers, and publishers. It may be used to deliver the content, troubleshoot, prevent fraud, provide reporting, perform internal analysis and product improvement, deliver ads and manage ad reporting and performance. In the case of content delivered through Third Party Services, Sirius XM collects and uses data derived from the listener of the Sirius XM Podcast Content, including IP address, in a non-personal manner and does not attempt to associate the information to you as an individual. We do not combine information associated to a particular IP address across other unaffiliated devices, applications or websites over time. Sirius XM may also use the content of podcast episodes to determine which ad or advertiser to place within the content, but Sirius XM does not collect, store or associate the podcast content with you as an individual person for advertising purposes.
11. General Audience Sites
Users must be 18 and older to sign up for use of the SiriusXM services. We do not knowingly collect any personal data from individuals younger than the age of 13.
12. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We reserve the right to change this Privacy Policy at any time. If we make material changes to our privacy policy, we will update the effective date and post a notice on the Services. We may also provide notice to you in other ways, such as through contact information you have provided, and provide you with the ability to opt-in or opt-out of the changes as required by law. Note that when applicable, you may need to consent to a revised policy in order to continue to use the Services. Your continued use of any of the Services after the effective date of the revised Privacy Policy will constitute your consent to those changes to the fullest extent allowed by applicable law.
