Privacy Policy
Your California Consumer Privacy Act Rights for Pandora
Your California Consumer Privacy Act Rights for SiriusXM
Effective December 20, 2024
This Privacy Policy (the “
Policy
”) describes the personal data collected and processed by Sirius XM Radio LLC and its subsidiaries, including Pandora Media, LLC (collectively, “
Sirius XM
,” “
we
” or “
us
”) through our consumer websites, apps and services (the “
Services
”). By accessing and using any of our Services, you agree to this Policy. The Services include:
Sirius XM satellite audio services, delivered under brand names SiriusXM and XM
SiriusXM streaming audio services
Pandora streaming audio services
SiriusXM specialty services such as marine, aviation weather, and traffic plans
Websites intended for retail consumers of Sirius XM and Pandora content and services, such as siriusxm.com, pandora.com, teamcoco.com, and 99percentinvisible.org, web players, applications, and platforms
SiriusXM and Pandora live and virtual events
The Services expressly do not include:
Safety and convenience connected vehicle services provided in-vehicle by our affiliate, SiriusXM Connect (formerly known as Sirius XM Connected Vehicle Services Inc.). Those connected vehicle services are provided in in conjunction with your vehicle manufacturer, operate independently of any Sirius XM audio services subscription, and are subject to a separate privacy policy offered by your vehicle manufacturer. Please refer to your vehicle owner’s manual or website for more information about data collected and used by the connected vehicle services.
Services provided by Sirius XM Canada Inc. Please refer to the Privacy Policy available on the Siriusxm.ca website for collection and use of personal data by Sirius XM Canada through its subscriptions and other services.
Audio services licensed by Sirius XM or Pandora to businesses for use by that business for its own customers, such as Pandora for Business.
Business to business advertising technology services provided by the Sirius XM affiliate company, AdsWizz Inc. and its subsidiaries, including Audio Ventures dba Simplecast. Relevant privacy notices for the AdsWizz business may be found at adswizz.com.
This Policy Does Not Apply to:
Personal data collected by the manufacturer of a connected speaker, TV or other device through which you access the Services
Personal data collected or use by anyone to whom you grant access directly
Personal data you instruct us to provide to a third party
In addition, please note: Sirius XM makes available certain podcast content under license to or ownership by Sirius XM, such as Team Coco and 99% Invisible podcasts (“
Sirius XM Podcast Content
”). Some Sirius XM Podcast Content is available to listeners, by listener choice, through websites, web players, applications or platforms not owned or controlled by Sirius XM, (each a “
Third Party Service
”). This Policy does not apply to the collection, use, or disclosure of your personal data by the third party who provides the Third Party Service when you choose to access Sirius XM Podcast Content through a Third Party Service; any such data collection and use is governed by the privacy notice of that third party. We recommend you familiarize yourself with the privacy notice of any Third Party Service you use to access Sirius XM Podcast Content. For more information on our data practices in connection with Sirius XM Podcast Content, please see the Section 10 below, "Supplemental Information For Listeners of Sirius XM Podcast Content."
This Policy is separate from and applies in addition to any terms for subscriptions, websites or other terms of use that apply to individual Services. Users of our Pandora services please see
here
and users of Sirius XM services please see
here
.
Sirius XM service users, please also review our
Customer Agreement
.
